,Recommended,266130,29026606,Posted: 4 January,all,Raven800,"It's not bad, but it's not the best Strategy Game I've played.Graphics and animations are acceptable, nothing too fancy. Gameplay and mechanics are easy to pick up with a ""straight to the point"" tutorial that teaches you what you need to know for first time players, and the experience and customization systems are fairly decent.How does the game play?It's a ""Pre-Planning"" style strategy game that's broken up into ""Phases"", Similar UFO or Frozen Synopsy. Simply put, you start each Phase by giving your soldiers orders, either to move from one location to another, deploy a grenade or equipment, etc. Once you have a pre-planned set of actions and routes set, you hit the ""Breach"" or ""Exicute"" button to watch it play it. It's a fairly basic system and it works fairly well, but the only problem I find with it is that the game's intro boasts about how this is supposedly a ""Realistic Tactics Simulator"" but if your soldiers are suddenly engaged by a new threat, rather than react accordingly or like in UFO halt their last action and pause for you to give them a new order to finish their phase, they just continue to follow the path set out for them. so if you give a soldier or soldiers to breach and clear a room and there's a wall of enemies on the other side waiting, your soldiers are going to continue walking into the hailstorm of bullets and taking hits instead of doing the more ""realistic"" thing and withdrawing back to cover.Aside from that though, it's a decent game. Would I recommend it? Sure, I can definely say that if you like turn based tactic games, give it a try. Personally I think another game like ""Door Kickers"" is a bit more ""realistic"" in terms of CQC Tactics, but this game is decent enough on its own.Overall Personal rating: Fair/Average. Nothing Too special about it, but can't find much bad about it either."
