,Recommended,266130,28109839,"Posted: 30 November, 2016",all,Sinking Tinnies,"First of all let me say, I wouldn't pay the full price for this game.. But if you're a fan of turn-based tactical strategy games & it is on sale, this game is a must buy. I'd probably describe this game as a stripped down version of X-COM. Instead of killing aliens around the globe, you are put in ""raid"" type scenarios against terrorists. Unlike X-COM though, there is no real story, you just complete missions & earn a number of stars depending on your performance. As you gain stars you unlock more levels, gear, etc. You earn silver each time you complete a mission, which you can use to to buy the new gear. You can make more than one squad & you can chose what Branch they are, such as SAS, SEALs & Rangers, etc. You're men level up allowing you to allocate points to certain attributes & they gain perks relative to what they specialise in. At the end of the day, this game is a fun strategy game with a heap of levels & difficulties to play on. The graphics, sounds and controls are basic, but good & overall the game is a great time killer. So I would definitely recommend this game if its ON SALE. I would not recommend it at the full price of $15 which in my opinion is a joke."
