,Not Recommended,266130,26753032,"Posted: 22 November, 2016",all,SoapyTarantula,"Like a simpler version of Doorkickers that uses turns instead of real-time. Unfortunately the amount of time a turn is, or what will happen during said turn, is never explained. As far as I can tell the turns end once all your characters are done moving.Its very much a weird mix of XCOM in the way your characters (or ""operators"" if you prefer) gain perks as they level up, and a weird mix of Doorkickers in regards to position and movement. The movement is controlled by the same button that moves the camera around, so prepare to accidentally swoosh the camera across the map instead of moving your unit a lot.The orders you can give your units are extremely simple. Move, move at this speed, look this direction, or use a perk/inventory item. That's all. There is no synching up actions to ""go-codes"" as in Doorkickers. I guess you could synch up actions by just doing them in the same turn but depending on the stats of your units things might not happen at the same time.Speaking of stats, you can slap all sorts of tacticool♥♥♥♥♥♥all over your units and their weapons. Each thing will affect the weapon or ""operator"" in someway, but it usually just ends up being ""+3 to Accuracy.""Probably my biggest gripe with this game is how hard it tries to be high-speed low-drag hooah operators operatin' operationally. From the intro cutscene to the voice lines to the unit photos it tries so hard to be gruff and tacticool that it just ends up coming off as comical, almost a parody. But I could only listen to what sounded like a teenager saying ""AREA SANITIZED"" so many times before it stopped being funny.This might be fun for an hour or so, I picked it up for 99% off. I couldn't see myself getting this for more than a few dollars."
