76561198122248263,Not Recommended,266130,16067311,"Posted: 29 May, 2015",all,I AM THE LIQUOR,"This game IS fun, but it is plagued by many problems.First and foremost, in my 20+ hours I've found so many glitches, little things that aren't necessarily game-ruining, but are VERY annoying; especially if you're a perfectionist like me (I HAVE to get 4 stars on every mission). An example being my medic unable to ""stabilize"" downed teammates. That isn't game-breaking, but it gets on my nerves. Sometimes I find my team shooting in the wrong direction. For instance, if I send them to an area looking a certain way, and they happen to pass up an enemy, sometimes my guys would just shoot in a random direction, then turn back towards the enemy and shoot, then back forward. I'm not sure what the point of leveling up ""reaction"" when your team doesn't even react to certain enemies. There is no real-time changing of position or anything like that, the game plays in turns. This isn't bad, it can just be annoying considering the enemy can run/advance MUCH faster than any of your guys (unless you level up speed to 100). Another thing I noticed is once in a while one of my guys, despite me having set a path for him, does not move at all that turn.As other reviewers have stated, this game feels unfinished. It really bugs me when developers let known glitches (like the medic 'stabilize' glitch) persist within a game and then work on a DLC. I know that the medic glitch is known because I saw a Facebook post for the app version of the game with comments from the devs to a guy who had brought it up. This game could be AMAZING if more things had been added. I feel like ""Doorkickers"" nailed it with the real-time movement and the fact that you can switch tactics on the fly instead of being stuck with whatever plan you chose.As for the positive, the game has a lot of customization features, which I love. It almost feels like an RPG. You can name each member of your squad, choose their profile pic/appearance, then buy and customize ALL of their gear. It's really neat. I also love the star system (you get rated on your performance on a mission by stars--1-4 stars). It makes the game kind of addicting, and adds replay value. The mission locations are unique and on each game mode, you must change your tactics. The game modes are: Terrorist Hunt (basically just sweep a level until you've killed all the terrorists), Bomb Defusal (defuse a bomb within the time limit), and a mode where you escape the map out of an extraction zone (your men are placed in random parts of the map).The game is by no means easy (on higher difficulty levels at least). Sometimes my fully-leveled squad struggled to clear certain levels, which I like. Challenges are good and as stated before, add replay value. The main reason I dislike this game is because it has many unfixed glitches/bugs, and it just feels unfinished.Final Verdict: 6.5/10Buy this game on sale and you won't regret it. Don't pay $15 for an app."
