76561198072380091,Recommended,266130,14059633,"Posted: 18 January, 2015",all,whatdoesthisbuttondo?,"If you are looking for deep tactical gameplay (as this game is advertised), then stay away, you won't find that here.That said, the game still offers good casual entertainment, if you enjoy leveling up your guys and unlocking new equipment, give it a spin.Quick run-down of the gameplay if you need help deciding if it is for you:You first create a squad, you can decide between some well-known specops units like DEVGRU, SAS, KSK and so on. What unit you select decides the starter attributes of your guys, one will have their special ability trained up nice, other will have reaction time up, other accuracy etc.Then you run through the missions, and I really mean run, as once you discover the one tactic that works 100% of the time against the AI, you'll just breeze through. Not much depth here, and the occasional weird glitch with your guys running backwards or facing a wall for no good reason.Your guys gain experience, and you get money, so in-between you level up your guys (in the end, it doesnt matter much what squad you made, they'll all end up the same just look different), buy them some new weapons and gear.You can upgrade weapons to modify their stats, but here you'll end up again with all the same upgrades as there is one good combination.Sounds like not much, but it is a decent enough time-killer, pick it up when it is on sale.In case 3d is not that important to you, I'd suggest to take a look at 'Door Kickers', that one has tactical gameplay down to perfection."
