,Recommended,266130,20112697,"Posted: 30 December, 2015",all,HuffingtonPants,"It's fine and all, fills a niche, but it's stale and lacks obvious features. It's a bit like a 3D version of Doorkickers (worth checking out if you're considering this).The combat is turn based, let's say you were storming a room with two entrances and lined up 2 guys outside each entrance. You might conceivably want them to storm the room at the same time, but alas, no, the only way to tell if that's going to happen is with a timeline style thing which runs across the characters move path. So on the floor on the otherside of the door might say 2 seconds. Well, on that 2 second mark you might want your other team to storm in. Unbelievably, there's no way to synchronise those events, by say, telling the other guy to pause for a second before proceeding. You could get him to run in circles before going through the door I guess, but then you hardly feel like a SWAT team. Another similarly stupid mechanic is that you cant order someone to go stand where someone else is stood, even if they're going to be 4 seconds down the hall before the other guy gets there. I think the real fun stems from the customisation and the content around that. Lots of maps, lots of guns, and a combat system that is just competent enough to be fun."
