76561198107377987,Recommended,266130,13932672,"Posted: 10 January, 2015",all,Cole_Train,"Let me begin by saying that this game is alright. There isn't anything seriously bad about it, but there isn't much that is great either.I bought this game during a sale for less than $5.00 and I don't think I would have paid more for it.It's fun little game, but it feels just a step above a java game that you could play on your browser. It's pretty addicting just like some of those simple games are as well.I haven't played a game like this before, but I hear that there are similar ones with more depth.--WHO THIS GAME IS FOR--Someone who is just interested in some casual tactical gaming. Pleased enough with moderate strategy gaming.The Good:++Levels aren't dreadfully long (about 6 minutes) but there are 7 countries to visit, each with 5 levels to play in. Also 3 game modes (Terrorist Hunt, Bomb Defusal, and Escape Plan) using same maps, This may not seem like alot but it manages to have just enough variety++There are a lot of options with costomization and I've found myself really thinking about my purchases for guns.--However, there is a problem with costomization that I will get into later++Option to play with Permanent death of squad members to earn extra XP (You get a replacement if one dies but you have to rank them back up) You keep the dead members expensive weapon equipment, which is good.++Upgrading skills for your soldiers is pretty solid with the variety of options (Responce, Accuracy, Health, Speed, Evation and an Skill that goes with the soldier's role; Like Squad Leader gets leadership skill you can upgrade). Not too easy to upgrade but not too hard.++I like that you can assign roles to your 4 person squad (Leader, Medic, Breach, ect) and that they get perks unlocked as you level up.The Bad:I'm going to begine with the costomization options++There are MANY different guns (some same price and same specs though)On the guns you can pack them with Optics, Lasers, Grips, Flashlights, Supressors, Gas System, and TriggersThe problem is that There are only a handful of attatchments in each category and it's easy to max out on the Optics, Lasers, Grips, Flashlights. There are no tactical thinking involved in these options because they only improve accuracy and have no negatives, so you don't weigh your options. -It's pretty mindless--The good thing is that Suppressors, Gas Systems,  and Triggers provide certain pros and cons that make you consider what perks you want and the expense of something.There are vests and other things but to buy that are important, but there are many items like clothing, goggles and facepaint that provide NO perks.++The Main Menu is slow and kinda laggy and brings a bad first impression when you put your mouse over a button and it takes 3 seconds for it to light up. The response when you select it is absolutely normal. But makes the game seem cheap.++The strategy is pretty basic. I've only felt trapped and in trouble a few times. The gameplay is mostly all about keeping your guys near cover and know how to split up your guys (which isn't challenging)If you 4 star all the maps as you progress Like I do and not jump ahead two counties (with harder soldiers) it doesn't stay very challenging. (I went two counties ahead and within two moves I was surounded and lost a guy right when he got shot at) -RIP Brett Breachers++I'm playing the levels in Germany, (which is the 4th country) and the environment is pretty static. Only a few levels actually had 1-3 of the soldiers walking around in real time as you plan out your strategy.THE UGLY++The ugly part isn't in the gameplay. It is with selecting items in the market and selecting the items when you choose a new gun or add attatchments.+The interface with the Market and costomization is terrible.+When I purchase a new gun I have to make sure to detatch everything on the previous gun, and there isn't any fast/easy way to do it (Such as putting a small 'x' in the corner). I have to select the icon individually for Lasers, Optics, Grips ect. THEN select to 'unequip' this gets very Tedious when there are 7 attachment types.+The interface only shows you the picture of what items are attached to your gun with no name of them or what their specs are.+You have to go to unequip it and then mouse over it to view its specs.+Another problem is that it doesn't tell you the name of what gun your soldier is equiped with. You have to memorize its shape and look in the market so you can compare it to a new weapon.+When you want to compare weapons in the market you can't do it side by side. You have to click the gun, then scoll down/up the list to view the next one. That is teious as well.CONCLUSION:I give the game a 6.5/10 -Would not pay $15.00, wait for a sale of less than $7 if you aren't sure about this. Addicting to play but almost too simple to call it a strategy game.+It needs improvements to make the game more interesting and needs its interface to be changed.+Would be interesting to add multiplayer of terrorists vs Spec Ops. Where each team has to make their moves and then it plays out.+Another request would be to add new scenarios (This might be later in the maps, IDK yet) with a less static environment and enemies. Like Helicopter, or enemies driving in the stronghold with vehicles."
