,Recommended,266130,24078802,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,Geekrider,"Breach and Clear is a slow, turn based CQB game involving strategic gameplay and excellent execution of level design and enemy placement. The game sets you in charge of a four-man fireteam tasked with various close-quarter missions of sweeping and killing, bomb defusal, and self-extraction. There are different classes (total 6) for your team members including 'Team Leader', 'Weapons Sergeant', 'Medic', 'Intelligence' etc. and each plays a specialized role. You can always create multiple squads with different classes so there is always a little variety in gameplay. Each class also has a starting perk and gains special abilities as you level up.Checking, clearing corners and finding cover is an integral part of the game. You can even control what I believe is called the ""sector of fire"" for each character while they are breaching. So there's a lot of nuance. The game has a pretty nice design throughout.  The levels are excellently designed in terms of flow and playability, and also have a good look and feel in terms of graphics.  The menus all look fine, the character design is acceptable and allows for customization, and the weapons themselves are customizable with special functions and color choices.If you're tired of the regular turn based RPG, this game provides a different spin on the genre. Give it a try. Breach and Clear is a solid title worth playing."
