,Recommended,266130,17818876,"Posted: 31 August, 2015",all,Dareon,"Solid tactical shootymans action, playable on old and underpowered hardware.  Design is tight and levels are short, if it took less time to load and exit I'd call it a coffee-break game. If you played X-COM Enemy Unknown/Within and thought the battles needed to be shorter and tighter, give this one a shot.The main draw for most people is probably going to be gun porn, there are dozens of gun and gear options, most of which only require the money you get from clearing missions.  Additional guns, however, are unlocked by scoring well on those missions.  It's a cumulative thing, so if you do horribly on 10-20 missions, you get the same gun as if you did great on five missions.  And of course you can replay the missions to get better rankings.Sound design is nothing to write home about. Guns go bang (or more of a clank when suppressed), terrorists go ow, your soldiers deliver canned soundbites, music is the generic vaguely patriotic military score.  It doesn't interfere with the experience."
