76561197994855401,Recommended,266130,17561362,"Posted: 15 August, 2015",all,Ishan451,"While I wouldn't necessarily compare the game to X-Com, neither new nor old, it is hard not to draw some parallels, considering both are Turnbased Tactics games. Breach & Clear has more in common with Frozen Synapse than it does have in common with X-Com though.The gameplay is rather simple. Enemies are randomly seeded into a map, where they will do their terroristy things like inspecting the carpet in an otherwise empty room, and you are tasked with clearing the bad guys, finding a hostage/bomb or escaping to an exfil location. The random seeding of the enemy gives the game quite a bit of replay-ability.Each level has one or more entry points and you as the player are tasked with dividing your 4 people team among the entry points and then go from there. You plan each move in its entirety and then once you have planned it, you execute said plan. Covering all the angels, trying to use cover to your advantage or throw flashbangs or regular grenades into an area to deal with the enemy.The game's simplicity is also its strength. Nobody ever said that chess was a boring game because it had a bunch of simple rules and Breach & Clear is like that as well. You do have a couple tactical options but for the most part its simple facing, facing and positioning, that wins the day.Graphically the game isn't impressive, but being a spiritual successor to Frozen Synapse it is still a step up from a blue backdrop and green and red enemies. Also I can't quite put my finger on it, why I am liking this game more than I did Frozen Synapse, but I also couldn't name any real difference between the two other than Breach & Clear having the more appealing aesthetic.Breach & Clear also offers a class and level system, with your team getting more experienced and unlocking more abilities. And there is a shop allowing you to buy new unlocked weapons, equipment and cosmetic items.All in all a solid game with, at the very least, the early missions taking about 10 to 15 minutes tops."
,Recommended,266130,17566457,"Posted: 16 August, 2015",all,Who am I?,"One of the best tactical RTS games I've bought for $3 CAD.The game does get repetative after a while (I am 1.5hrs into and already getting a bit repetative), and the graphics are a bit dated. Also, the gun shots will scare you - make sure to turn your volume down...However, the soundtrack is pretty good; customazition of your squad is fairly deep; the game is easy to grasp; simple gameplay, and it doesn't try anything too complicated.TL;DRIf this game is on sale, get it. If not, wait for it to go on sale."
