76561198006061781,Recommended,266130,17558593,"Posted: 15 August, 2015",all,Juggernut,"The reason why i bought it the 80% off but I must say I am very impressed by this rather small game.It is turned based and resembles the XCOM franchise but with a some big differences. Instead of being limited to one action each round every soldier can take out as many enemy soldiers they spott on their route. The time limit makes you wanna repeat the different missions to beat you previous time. Earn money and buy new gear. Gain XP and lvl your team up, Try different tactics and refine your squad line up. All is possible in the pursuit of killing bandits.Straight forward instructions and easy to learn.Very fine balance between tactics and fast game play.So if you enjoy the XCOM franchise pick this game up.Rating: 4.5/5"
,Recommended,266130,17560715,"Posted: 15 August, 2015",all,caluyadiver,"Strangely addictive tactical SimulationBreach & Clear is a small squad based tactical simulation.You manage a Squad of 4 soldiers to fulfill different technical scenarios.- Terrorist hunt (clear all hostiles),- Bomb Squad (Find and defuse one or multiple Bombs)- Escape Plan (where your Squad is separated all over the map and has to reunite and find a way out alive.- One scenario takes around 2-10 min.- You can go loud (breach the doors with explosives) our stealth.- RPG elements, your squad has ability progression. like accuracy, reaction, health etc..- 6 different classes, every class has some specialties (Healing, 360 shoot, 2 Grenades etc.). they do not really matter until you start playing on higher difficulty. if you try to master the game on insane, your class choice and composition of your squad will differ from scenario to scenario type.- in-game marketplace with a decent amount of different weapons and equipment to personalize your squadOverall it is strangely addictive, I do highly recommend the game.The game has a high re-playability I come back to it over and over again. if you like tactical games, military scenarios and turn-based gameplay and you are looking for an entertaining game which does not absorb you for days, that's the game you are looking for. especially if it is on sale, grab it! you will have fun for at least 10hours. some achievements are a bit grindy, if you wanne go for 100% completion you will need at least 60h+."
