76561198027069676,Recommended,266130,32262193,Posted: 7 June,all,FlameJet,"This is a completionist game. Military turn based strategy. if you need more story than strategy, probably wont have much fun. You can manage a small squad through a skirmish / map, and control several variables inside of that. Trying different squad combinations (all shotgun crew, or 2 snipes and 2 heavy guners, etc), skill tree / talents, and with those you can get really invested into your team, IF you want to. if you just want to beat the game, it wont take long. If you want to get highest score in each campain, you'll have fun.typical turn:setup - chose your team and their equipment, such as drones, medpacks, etc. chose your starting point for each soldier. you can chose all 4 to burst into one door, or 2 teams of 2, however you like.  (if applicable in the game type. some, you start spread out on the map and try to escape).turn planning - you pick one of your troops. you have a movement distance, so you chose where you want him to go. you chose how: sprinting, walking, etc. you chose WHERE HE LOOKS during that movement. you can get really specific with this, as in, take to steps, look left down that hall, take 2 more steps, look straight, last 2 steps, look right. i havent played another game that allows this, and it's smooth transitions between focal points. try to put your guy's head on a swivel, and he'll probably see nothing, but have him cover a direction, walk with a squadmate that covers the other direction. you chose where you want to toss a grenade, or who you want to use the medpack on an injured comrade. once you got your turn planned, you execute itexecution - you click the go button, and watch your plan unfold, did you have your guy looking the wrong way? did you have 1 soldier toss a flashbang while another walked right past him into the blast radius? did you sneak past the sniper without taking a shot in the face? could you have got that 1 bad guy hiding in the corner without losing a solider if you had come in a different entrance?If you enjoy trying to get the best possible outcome with different setups of teams, using different styles of play, you'll have fun. If you need to know why the shotgunner carries a shotgun, or if you need backstory on the captian of the barge you're clearing out, you probably wont. It's a Turn-Based military strategy game from a commanders view, and not much more."
